  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. The key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Disguising the origin of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the legitimate economy as seemingly legal assets\n\nLegal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most countries have laws criminalizing these activities under financial crime statutes.",
